threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is an IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of Mirai or Gafgyt, targeting MIPS-based embedded devices. It exhibits several definitive malicious behaviors: 1) Telnet credential brute-forcing via an extensive hardcoded list of usernames and passwords found in sub_40fd00 (e.g., 'root/Pon521', 'admin/1234', 'vizxv'); 2) Remote file propagation and execution using busybox utilities like wget, tftp, and ftpget to download payloads (sub_40f8f8); 3) Use of DNS-over-HTTPS (DoH) for stealthy C2 communication, seen in sub_40bbd8's HTTP template for '/dns-query'; and 4) Anti-analysis and process scanning via recursive iteration of the '/proc' filesystem and process maps (sub_40a314, sub_4004c8). The binary also contains logic for backgrounding itself and persisting on the target device.
